arch:property.oc:show_val: Flot. 2, (4189), >4mm, 100% sorted, diagnostics only This is a small-medium size unit of light to medium (towards the light) brown bone. It is slightly weathered with less than 5% burning, some digestion and no abrasion. There is one long bone shaft with a smooth rounded tip and polished edges, which appear to have been caused by trampling rather than use however, most of the material does not look trampled or rolled. Most of the unit is 03 long bone fragments with an average length of 2 to 3 cm. Small amounts of ribs and vertebra and very few diagnostic limb bones are present and a good number of teeth and feet. Taxa include one equid carpal, a few cattle bones and lots of caprine bones. There is one large bird scapula, which has been sent to Cornell for identification. Overall the material is mixed post-butchery and post-consumption waste - if denser it could be midden-like. Last Number = F154

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
